0c4465ba-072d-4eaf-90db-8addbbc8b297.do_description: To make the output, you have to...take the pattern and mirror it to the four corners like a reflection instead of a copy. One color will have 2 blocks of that color. Use that color to make a square around the grid using one for the start and the other for the end. This square will skip one block and then place a block all the way around the grid. If it encounters the patterns that you placed down skip that square
0c4465ba-072d-4eaf-90db-8addbbc8b297.grid_description: The output grid size...should be the same as the input

2371e151-f295-4263-af3a-574b839ba3a0.do_description: To make the output, you have to...continue the established pattern, leaving one black square between each colored square in the pattern.

49913dd5-f947-48f2-99b8-aaa793efa27b.do_description: To make the output, you have to...create border using first two color boxes with the second box to the right being the main boxes and first box is the corner boxes. The border should start one block to the right and one block down and leave a space in between each block and all the sides. The last two blocks should create a diagonal from the box on the corner and the diagonal should continue with last box
49913dd5-f947-48f2-99b8-aaa793efa27b.grid_description: The output grid size...input size is same

50892c81-f43e-483a-86a5-0211dd874443.do_description: To make the output, you have to... take the main color and create a border frame from the location it is in. take the color next to it and put it on the end point of the border frame. take the color box that is further away and copy that into the 4 directions making sure they are mirror images. A black box should be between each color box.
50892c81-f43e-483a-86a5-0211dd874443.grid_description: The output grid size... keep it the same

6e5b692b-f905-4bec-b0c7-4c02bac0b5f5.do_description: To make the output, you have to... place a set of the colored boxes in each corner, but rotate the boxes so it is a mirror of the original set. For example, if a red box is nearest to the middle in the original set, then in the corners the red box will also be nearest to the middle. Next you will then create a border with the two same colored boxes that border another box. Just repeat those boxes away from the group until they go to another corner.
